The method `ping` should return an integer representing the number of requests that have happened in the past 3000 milliseconds (including the new request).
The method `ping` should add the new request at time `t` to the list of requests.
The list of requests should be updated to include the new request.
The range of requests should be updated to include the new request.
The method `ping` should return the number of requests that have happened in the inclusive range `[t - 3000, t]`.
